 industry in other to improve upon her skills to act good movies.<ref name=\":1\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.ghanacelebrities.com/2010/03/17/exclusive-interview-with-ghanaian-actress-vicky-zugah/|title=Exclusive Interview With Ghanaian Actress-Vicky Zugah|date=2010-03-17|website=GhanaCelebrities.Com|language=en-US|access-date=2020-04-02}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.google.com/search?client=ubuntu&hs=ydq&channel=fs&sxsrf=ALeKk01_N2gSr_h7zR4RG3n72qovlUm8hw:1585865133120&ei=rWGGXoL-Brue1fAPwbOquA4&q=vicky+zugah+biography&oq=vicky+zugah&gs_lcp=CgZwc3ktYWIQARgBMgQIIxAnMgQIIxAnMgcIABAUEIcCMgQIABBDMgYIABAHEB4yAggAMgIIADICCAAyBggAEAcQHjICCABQAFgAYKTSA2gAcAB4AIABkwaIAZULkgEFNS0xLjGYAQCqAQdnd3Mtd2l6&sclient=psy-ab|title=vicky zugah biography - Google Search|website=www.google.com|access-date=2020-04-02}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://ghanatrade.com.gh/Latest-News/xclusiv-fotos-actress-vicky-zugah-celebrates-her-birthday-with-flowery-dress.html|title=XCLUSIV FOTOS: Actress Vicky Zugah Celebrates Her Birthday With Flowery Dress|last=Administrator|website=Ghana Trade  - Official SME Product Portal and Web Gallery|language=en-gb|access-date=2020-04-02}}</ref>\n\n== Filmography ==\nList of movies she has acted over the years.<ref name=\":1\" /><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.imdb.com/name/nm2990351/bio|title=Victoria Zugah|website=IMDb|access-date=2020-04-02}}</ref>\n\n* Trokosi\n* Total Exchange\n* Cross My Heart\n* My Darling Princess\n* June 4th\n* Araba Lawson\n* Big Girl Club\n* Girls Connection\n* True Colour\n* Pretty Queen\n* Tears of Womanhood\n* The Return of Beyonce\n* The  Bible\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:21st-century Ghanaian actresses]]\n[[Category:Ghanaian film actresses]]\n\n{{Ghana-stub}}\n", "name_user": "Jwale2", "label": "safe", "comment": "Added Info box", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Vicky_Zugah"}
{"title_page": "1959\u201360 Norwegian Main League", "text_new": "{{Infobox football league season\n| competition        = [[Eliteserien|Hovedserien]]\n| season             = 1959\u201360\n| winners            = [[Fredrikstad FK|Fredrikstad]]<br />8th title\n| relegated          = [[SK Brann|Brann]]<br>[[IK Start|Start]]<br>[[Raufoss Fotball|Raufoss]]<br>[[SK Brage|Brage]]\n| continentalcup1    = [[1960\u201361 European Cup|European Cup]] \n| continentalcup1 qualifiers = Fredrikstad\n| matches            = \n| total goals        = \n| highest attendance = \n| lowest attendance  = \n| average attendance = \n| prevseason         = [[1958\u201359 Norwegian Main League|1958\u201359]]\n| nextseason         = [[1960\u201361 Norwegian Main League|1960\u201361]]\n}}\nThe '''1959\u20131960 [[Eliteserien|Hovedserien]]''' was the 15th completed season of top division [[association football|football]] in [[Norway]].\n\n==Overview==\nIt was contested by 16 teams, and [[Fredrikstad FK|Fredrikstad]] won the championship, their eighth league title. This was the first season a bronze medal was awarded.\n\n==Teams and locations==\n:''Note: Table lists in alphabetical order.\n{| border=\"0\"\n| valign=\"top\" |\n\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" border=\"1\"\n|+Group A\n|-\n! Team\n!{{Tooltip| Ap. | Appearances in top divisions of Norwegian football}}<!--Begins with 1937\u201338 season. Abandoned 1939\u201340 season does not count.-->\n! Location\n|-\n| [[SK Brann|Brann]]\n| align=\"center\"| '''12'''\n| [[Bergen]]\n|-\n| [[Gre\u00e5ker IF|Gre\u00e5ker]]\n| align=\"center\"| '''2'''\n| [[Sarpsborg]]\n|-\n| [[Larvik Turn & IF|Larvik Turn]]\n| align=\"center\"| '''11'''\n| [[Larvik]]\n|-\n| [[Lillestr\u00f8m SK|Lillestr\u00f8m]]\n| align=\"center\"| '''10'''\n| [[Lillestr\u00f8m]]\n|-\n| [[Sandefjord BK]]\n| align=\"center\"| '''14'''\n| [[Sandefjord]]\n|-\n| [[IK Start|Start]]\n| align=\"center\"| '''4'''\n| [[Kristiansand]]\n|-\n| [[V\u00e5lerenga Fotball|V\u00e5lerengen]]\n| align=\"